sentences: Elias Melka Geresu (Amharic: ኤሊያስ መልካ ገረሱ; 10 December 1977 – 4 October 2019) was an Ethiopian record producer and songwriter.
Elias became popular after successfully composing Teddy Afro's debut album Abugida, which was released in 2001.
Until his death on 4 October 2019, he had played a crucial role in the Ethiopian music industry.
Melka, having struggled with diabetes and kidney complications, died on 4 October 2019.
